# Force LF line endings for all text files in the working tree, on all
# platforms. Without this, Windows runners with the default
# core.autocrlf=true convert checked-out files (.md fixtures, .ts source,
# etc.) to CRLF — and snapshot tests that compare turndown output (always
# LF) against fixture content fail with a pure line-ending diff.
#
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect text vs. binary; `eol=lf` forces LF in
# the working tree even on Windows. The convention follows the
# .gitattributes pattern documented at
# https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/git-basics/configuring-git-to-handle-line-endings.
* text=auto eol=lf
